<p>Good day. I am currently learning XSLT 2.0. I would like to pull a data that comes from multi similar tags. Like the one below</p>  <p>Here is my XSLT :</p>  <pre><code>&lt;xsl:for-each select="/root1/root2"&gt;      &lt;xsl:for-each select="a1 | b1"&gt;            &lt;xsl:value-of select="c1"&gt;            &lt;xsl:value-of select="a1"&gt;            &lt;xsl:value-of select="b1"&gt;      &lt;/xsl:for-each&gt; &lt;/xsl:for-each&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Input XML:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;root1&gt;     &lt;root2&gt;         &lt;a1&gt;Car1&lt;/a1&gt;         &lt;a1&gt;Car2&lt;/a1&gt;         &lt;a1&gt;Car3&lt;/a1&gt;          &lt;b1&gt;Red&lt;/b1&gt;         &lt;b1&gt;Blue&lt;/b1&gt;         &lt;b1&gt;Black&lt;/b1&gt;         &lt;c1&gt;Name&lt;/c1&gt;     &lt;/root2&gt; &lt;/root&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Desired Output:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Name Car1 Red</p>      <p>Name Car2 Blue</p>      <p>Name Car3 Black</p> </blockquote>  <p>I could not even pull up Name with my XSLT</p>  <p>How do I pair up a1 with the correct b1?</p>  <p>Any suggestion?</p>